{
  "stem": "4361.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was hit a couple of times, and an elderly woman who was much younger then than I am now-- must've been-- to me, she was an elderly lady, probably in her mid 30s-- came to me and said in Hungarian, child, why are you crying so?",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I said, my diploma-- they took away my diploma.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she said, forget it, because what you have in your head, that they cannot take away.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you know, that has stayed with me too as one of the human things, humane things, one of the decent things that I remembered, one of the few decent things that I remembered that happened in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, eventually my sobs subsided, and then we were pushed into the shower room, disinfected, sprayed with disinfectant, and taken into another place.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were given some rags, which were supposed to be dresses, skirts, no underwear, nothing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I got a pair of shoes, two lefties, so it was really-- I mean, for Halloween, you don't get dressed that way.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But that's what we had, because we had nothing else.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And by this time, it's morning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The smell is there, and now we see not so much flames but smoke.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Ah, now we know why the smell.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's a bakery.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were baking bread.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Strange smell, but that's what it is.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You see the chimneys.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now we see chimneys.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Next thing is that I look at someone, and I burst out laughing, because we looked surreal-- shaven, in rags.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean I remember there was some sort of a window, and a couple of us went to look at ourselves, and we could not recognize ourselves, so we each had to move our heads to know who was who, because it was really not a madhouse.",
      "word_count": 47
    }
  ],
